    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix client connection handling in RF simulator to prevent buffer overflow\n\n### Summary\nThe RF simulator's client handling code was using file descriptor values directly as array indices when managing client connections. This caused buffer overflow issues when file descriptors had large values, leading to crashes and undefined behavior during client connections.\n\nThis fix implements a proper mapping between file descriptors and buffer indices to prevent out-of-bounds array access.\n\n### Changes\n- `radio/rfsimulator/simulator.c`: \n  * Added `fd_to_buf_map` array to map file descriptors to buffer indices\n  * Modified `allocCirBuf` to find free buffer slots and create proper mappings\n  * Modified `removeCirBuf` to use mappings and clear them properly\n  * Updated `socketError` to use the mapping system\n  * Modified data receiving code in `flushInput` to use mappings\n  * Added proper initialization of the mapping array\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original issue:\n1. Start the RF simulator in server mode\n2. Connect multiple clients rapidly to force higher file descriptor values\n3. Observe crashes or memory corruption when file descriptor values exceed the buffer array size\n\nThe fix ensures stable client connection handling regardless of assigned file descriptor values.\n"
}